articles.author: Liz Lee, Andrew Hayley
articles.description: China's involvement in Russia's Arctic LNG-2 liquefied natural gas project should not be the target of any third party intervention or restrictions, its foreign ministry said on Tuesday.
articles.title: China criticizes U.S. sanctions on Russia's Arctic LNG-2 project

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Israel's government agreed to give Intel Corp (INTC.O) a $3.2 billion grant for new $25 billion chip plant it plans to build in southern Israel, both sides said on Tuesday.
articles.title: Intel to get $3.2 billion government grant for new $25 billion Israel chip plant

articles.author: Naveen Thukral
articles.description: High food prices in recent years have prompted farmers worldwide to plant more cereals and oilseeds, but consumers are set to face tighter supplies well into 2024, amid adverse El Nino weather, export restrictions and higher biofuel mandates.
articles.title: Global 2024 staple food supplies to be strained by dry weather, export curbs

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: AstraZeneca (AZN.L) said on Tuesday it will buy China-based Gracell Biotechnologies (GRCL.O) for up to $1.2 billion as the Anglo-Swedish pharma company furthers its cell therapy ambitions.
articles.title: AstraZeneca to buy China-based Gracell Biotechnologies in $1.2 billion deal

articles.author: Li Gu, Casey Hall
articles.description: A slew of smaller Chinese gaming companies have announced share buybacks - plans seen as an attempt to reassure investors after the market was spooked by regulatory moves to clamp down on consumer spending on games.
articles.title: Chinese gaming firms unveil share buybacks after regulatory move unnerves investors

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Shares of Infosys (INFY.NS) fell as much as 2.6% on Tuesday after the company said that an unnamed global company, which had signed a $1.5 billion deal focused on artificial intelligence solutions, decided to terminate its Memorandum of Understanding (MoU) with the IT giant.
articles.title: India's Infosys falls after $1.5 bln AI deal termination

articles.author: Ankur Banerjee
articles.description: Asian stocks crept higher on Tuesday and the dollar lurked near a five-month low as cooling U.S. inflation bolstered bets the Federal Reserve would cut interest rates early next year.
articles.title: Asian stocks rise, dollar drifts as US rate cut bets rise

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Ukraine carried out an air attack on Feodosia in Crimea, Ukraine's air force commander said on Tuesday, after the Russian-installed governor of the Crimea said that the assault sparked a fire in the town's port area.
articles.title: Ukraine carries out air assault on Crimea's port of Feodosia

articles.author: Nidal Al-Mughrabi, Bassam Masoud, Emily Rose
articles.description: Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu vowed to keep up the fight against Hamas militants, but a United Nations humanitarian team leader said Palestinian civilians in Gaza who honor Israeli evacuation orders cannot be guaranteed they will be safe.
articles.title: Netanyahu vows no let-up in war but UN worker says Gazans have no place to go

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Ethiopia became Africa's third default in as many years on Tuesday after it failed to make a $33 million "coupon" payment on its only international government bond.
articles.title: Ethiopia becomes Africa's latest sovereign default
